Now I'm not trying to to say I speak for every person on this website. Speaking for someone else without their permission would be disrespectful, which I am not. I am just wondering why you would not simply add the tag I mentioned above to ease the frustration of searching for specific doujins. It would be as simple as to search for the tag then add it, which would let many others who are left in the dark about this piece of erotic art experience a superior form of doujin. One that is wholesome, full color and animated. This is a violation of their rights on this platform for eromanga, or as it is called in non-japanese speaking countries, hentai.
